cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper proposes a computational method to generate appealing brand names based on the description of entities. The approach involves using quantitative scores for readability, pronounceability, memorability, and uniqueness of the generated names to rank order them. This suggests that the paper could belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This sub-category deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics, which are relevant to the task of generating brand names based on descriptions. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category deals with the development of intelligent agents and systems, which could be relevant to the proposed computational method for generating brand names. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category deals with the development of algorithms and models that can learn from data, which could be relevant to the proposed method for ranking the generated brand names. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): This sub-category deals with the retrieval of relevant information from large collections of data, which could be relevant to the task of generating brand names based on descriptions. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): This sub-category deals with the social and ethical implications of computing, which could be relevant to the impact of brand names on society and culture.
